<p><a name="Imperative_present" id="Imperative_present"></a></p>
<h4><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Latin_conjugation&amp;action=edit&amp;section=12" title="Edit section: Imperative present">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Imperative present</span></h4>
<p>The imperative in the present conveys commands, pleas and recommendations. <i>Portā</i> can be translated as "(You) Carry" or simply, "Carry." The imperative present occurs only in the second person.</p>
<ul>
<li>The second person singular in the active voice uses only the bare stem, and does not add an imperative ending.</li>
</ul>
<table class="wikitable">
<tr bgcolor="#EFEFEF">
<th rowspan="3"></th>
<th colspan="8"><b>Imperative Active Present</b></th>
