<td>audīvissent</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>As always, the passive voice uses the perfect passive participle. The subjunctive imperfect of <i>esse</i> is used here. <i>Portātus essem</i> may mean "I should have been carried," or "I could have been carried," in the conditional sense.</p>
